    body: "Vespers is the second major hinge of the Liturgy of the Hours, prayed as daylight fades. Its structure mirrors Lauds: a hymn, two psalms, a New Testament canticle, a short reading, the Magnificat (Canticle of Mary), intercessions, the Our Father, and a concluding prayer. In solemn celebrations the altar may be incensed during the Magnificat. The evening setting evokes the lighting of lamps—symbolizing Christ as the Light of the World—and the offering of evening sacrifice (Psalm 141:2). Vespers was historically the most attended public office in medieval parishes and cathedrals.",
