    body: "The Catechism (CCC 2088-2089) identifies several sins against the virtue of faith. Voluntary doubt is the deliberate refusal to assent to what God has revealed and the Church teaches (distinct from involuntary difficulties or questions in faith, which are not sinful). Incredulity is the neglect or willful refusal of revealed truth. Heresy is the obstinate denial after baptism of a truth that must be believed with divine and Catholic faith. Apostasy is the total repudiation of the Christian faith. Schism is the refusal to submit to the Pope or to maintain communion with the members of the Church subject to him. Each sin wounds not only the individual but the entire Body of Christ.",
