    body: "The corporal works of mercy (feeding the hungry, giving drink to the thirsty, clothing the naked, sheltering the homeless, visiting the sick, visiting prisoners, burying the dead) address material human needs. The spiritual works (instructing the ignorant, counseling the doubtful, admonishing sinners, bearing wrongs patiently, forgiving offenses, comforting the afflicted, praying for the living and the dead) address needs of the soul. Together they form a comprehensive program of Christian charity that engages the whole person. Jesus identified the corporal works with service to Himself (Matt 25:31-46), and the tradition of the Church has always insisted that both types are necessary—one cannot separate love of body from love of soul.",
