    oneLiner: "God's unconditional promise to David that his throne would be established forever, fulfilled in Jesus Christ as the eternal Davidic King.",
    body: "In 2 Samuel 7, God promises David through the prophet Nathan that his son will build a house for the Lord, and God will establish that son's kingdom forever. Unlike the Mosaic covenant, which was conditional on Israel's obedience, the Davidic covenant is unconditional—God swears by Himself that David's line will endure. The New Testament presents Jesus as the fulfillment of this covenant: the angel Gabriel tells Mary her son will be given 'the throne of his father David' and 'of his kingdom there will be no end' (Luke 1:32-33). Catholic theology sees the Church as the restored Davidic kingdom, with Christ as its eternal King and the Pope as the successor of the Davidic prime minister (Isaiah 22:22; Matt 16:19).",
