    tags: ["covenant", "abraham", "promise", "gentiles"],
    oneLiner: "The progressive realization of God's threefold promise to Abraham—land, descendants, and universal blessing—culminating in Christ and the Church.",
    body: "God's covenant with Abraham (Gen 12, 15, 17, 22) contained three promises: a land, descendants as numerous as the stars, and blessing for all nations. Catholic theology traces the fulfillment of these promises through Israel's history and into the New Testament. The land promise finds its ultimate fulfillment not in mere territory but in the new heavens and new earth. The promise of descendants is fulfilled in the Church, where all who share Abraham's faith become his children (Gal 3:29). The universal blessing reaches completion when the Gospel goes out to all nations. Paul's Letter to the Galatians is the definitive New Testament commentary on how Christ fulfills the Abrahamic covenant.",
