    body: "The prophetic books span from the eighth century BC (Amos, Hosea, Isaiah, Micah) through the post-exilic period (Haggai, Zechariah, Malachi). The prophets served as God's spokesmen, not primarily predicting the future but calling Israel back to covenant faithfulness. Their message had three recurring themes: judgment on injustice and idolatry, a call to repentance, and hope in God's ultimate restoration. Catholic interpretation recognizes a 'fuller sense' (sensus plenior) in many prophetic texts, seeing in them foreshadowings of Christ, the Church, and the end times that exceeded the human author's original awareness. The Lectionary draws heavily on prophetic texts during Advent and Lent.",
