    body: "The Examen (sometimes called the Examination of Consciousness, distinct from an examination of conscience) is the prayer St. Ignatius considered most essential—he told Jesuits that if they had to skip one prayer, it should not be this one. The five steps are: (1) place yourself in God's presence and ask for light; (2) give thanks for the gifts of the day; (3) review the day's events, noticing where God was present and where you responded or failed to respond; (4) express sorrow for failings and ask forgiveness; (5) look forward to tomorrow and ask for grace. The key innovation is that the Examen focuses not just on sins but on the entire texture of the day—consolations, desolations, desires, and movements of the heart—to discern the Spirit's guidance.",
