    oneLiner: "The spirituality of the Order of Preachers, integrating contemplation and study in service of preaching the truth for the salvation of souls.",
    body: "Dominican spirituality is captured in the Order's motto: Veritas (Truth) and its mission statement: contemplata aliis tradere ('to hand on to others the fruits of contemplation'). Founded by St. Dominic de Guzman in 1216 to combat heresy through preaching, the Dominican tradition uniquely integrates intellectual rigor with contemplative prayer. Its pillars are: study as a form of prayer and service; liturgical prayer (the Dominicans were instrumental in developing the Office); communal life as a support for preaching; and a commitment to doctrinal truth. The Order's greatest intellectual achievement is St. Thomas Aquinas's Summa Theologiae. Dominican spirituality also fostered the Rosary, which tradition attributes to a vision given to St. Dominic by the Blessed Virgin.",
